The paper focuses on object and face detection in poor visibility conditions, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of low-level vision techniques to benefit high-level automatic visual recognition, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The benchmark sets and baseline results reported in the paper involve machine learning models, indicating a potential overlap with the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the collection of real-world data, which could be relevant to the subfield of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper discusses the enhancement of images, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
